                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17280717-18-off80 t17280717-18-crimeloc82"></join>, in June last, and the Prisoner being there in the Country for 2 or 3 Weeks, and pretending to go for London on the Day before his Mare was stolen, he suspected him to have taken it; upon which he came to London, and found out the Prisoner at Bloomsbury, when he confess'd be stole it, and sold it to one Mr. Wood, but begg'd the Prosecutor would not take the Law of him, for he had Friends at Totenhem which would make him Satisfaction, but he going there they refused it.</p>
               <p>
            
